In Fig. 2 the size of twin-vortices is plotted against the Reynolds num· bers, and from this curve the critical Reynolds number can be deduced.
It may be concluded that the critical Reynolds number at which the twin-vortices begin to form in the rear of a circular cylinder is 5.
Further, the experiments indicate that the wall effect of the tank can be neglected when d/D<l/50 (where d is the diameter of the cylinder and D is the tank width).
An experiment using microscopic photography, for the determination of more accurate value of the critical Reynolds number, will be carried out in the near future.

